# Responsive & Touch Layout

## Three surfaces

| Surface | App | Width strategy |
|---------|-----|----------------|
| Mobile H5 | `apps/h5` | Mobile-first, full width, safe-area insets |
| Pad | `apps/web` | `pad:` variant (≥768px) |
| PC | `apps/web` | `pc:` variant (≥1440px) |

MatePad Pro landscape (~1440px CSS) must use **Pad layout**, not PC. Use `pc:` at 1440px, not Tailwind `xl` (1280px).

## Breakpoints (canonical)

```typescript
// apps/web/src/config/site.ts — single source of truth for JS logic
export const BREAKPOINTS = { pad: 768, pc: 1440 } as const;
```

Tailwind custom variants (`packages/ui/src/styles/globals.css`):

- `pad:` → `@media (min-width: 768px)`
- `pc:` → `@media (min-width: 1440px)`
- `pointer-coarse:` → touch devices
- `hover-hover:` → devices with real hover

When changing breakpoints, update **both** `site.ts` and `globals.css` `@custom-variant`.

## Layout rules

**apps/web**

- `<768px`: single-column fallback; soft H5 hint only — never block usage
- `768–1439px`: Pad layout (collapsed sidebar, 2-column grids)
- `≥1440px`: PC layout (expanded sidebar, 3-column grids)

**apps/h5**

- Use `H5Shell` with safe-area padding; full-width buttons by default

## Touch vs hover

Decouple **width** from **input capability**:

```tsx
<button className="min-h-11 min-w-11 hover-hover:hover:bg-accent active:scale-[0.98]" />
<div className="pointer-coarse:gap-4 gap-2" />
```

Minimum touch target: **44px** (`min-h-11 min-w-11`). See `TOUCH_TARGET_MIN` in `config/theme.ts`.

## Don'ts

- Don't use `xl:` (1280px) for PC layout in web app
- Don't put mobile-only flows in `apps/web` — use `apps/h5`
- Don't rely on `:hover` alone for critical affordances on Pad
